\begin{document}$$ \gamma  = \frac{{\phi _{A} \eta _{A} }} {{\phi _{D} \eta _{D} }} $$\end{document} is a parameter to correct for photophysical properties of the dyes. ΦA and ΦD are acceptor and donor quantum yield, and ηA and ηD are acceptor and donor detector efficiency respectively. As a first approximation γ was set to unity.

A more accurate estimate for γ was obtained from experimental intensity time traces where donor bleaching took place after acceptor bleaching. In these cases the FRET efficiency could also be calculated from donor quenching:
